casebody.data:
Javontea JONES, Appellant,
v.
STATE of Missouri, Respondent. WD 79960 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: March 13, 2018 Lara M. Guscott and Annette Wallace, Assistant Appellate Defenders, Kansas City, MO, Attorneys for Appellant. Joshua D. Hawley, Attorney General, and Christine Lesicko, Assistant Attorney General, Jefferson City, MO, Attorneys for Respondent. Before Division IV: Mark D. Pfeiffer, Chief Judge, and Victor C. Howard and Cynthia L. Martin, Judges

Order

Per Curiam:

Mr. Javontea Jones appeals from the judgment of the Circuit Court of Clay County, Missouri, denying, after an evidentiary hearing, his Rule 24.035 amended motion for post-conviction relief based on ineffective assistance of plea counsel. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum of law has been provided to the parties. The judgment is affirmed. Rule 84.16(b).
